To fork the Mediator Jekyll theme into your own GitHub repository and create your professional website, follow these step-by-step instructions:
Fork the Mediator theme repository
Go to the Mediator theme repository on GitHub: https://github.com/dirkfabisch/mediator
Click on the "Fork" button in the top-right corner of the page.
Select your GitHub account as the destination for the fork.
Clone your forked repository
Go to your forked repository on GitHub: https://github.com/yourusername/mediator
Click on the green "Code" button and copy the URL for your forked repository.
Open your terminal/command prompt and navigate to the directory where you want to store your website files.
Run the following command to clone your forked repository:
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/mediator.git
Install Jekyll and Bundler
Ensure you have Ruby installed on your system.
Install Jekyll and Bundler by running: gem install jekyll bundler
Install theme dependencies
Navigate into the cloned repository: cd mediator
Run bundle install to install the required gems for the theme.
Run Jekyll locally
From within the mediator directory, run: bundle exec jekyll serve
Open your web browser and visit http://localhost:4000 to see the Mediator theme.
Customize the theme
Open the _config.yml file and update the site settings like title, description, url, etc.
Modify the HTML/CSS in the _layouts and _includes directories to change the theme's appearance.
Add your content by creating new Markdown files in the _posts directory for blog posts, or in the root for pages.
Commit and push changes
Use git add . to stage your changes.
Commit your changes with git commit -m "Initial customizations".
Push your changes to your forked repository: git push origin main
Enable GitHub Pages
Go to your forked repository on GitHub: https://github.com/yourusername/mediator
Navigate to Settings > Pages.
Under "Source", select the "main" branch and click "Save".
View your website
GitHub will now build your Jekyll site from the contents of your repository.
Once the build is complete, you can access your website at https://yourusername.github.io/mediator
By following these steps, you have forked the Mediator Jekyll theme into your own GitHub repository, customized it to your liking, and published your professional website using GitHub Pages.
